@{ Layout = null; }
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Dancing+Script&family=Inter:wght@300;400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/skolar-dialog.css">
    <title>Learner Terms and Conditions | Skolar</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="~/assets/img/skolarlogo.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/main-css/terms.css">
</head>
<body>
    <script src="~/js/skolar-dialog.js"></script>

    <main class="terms-page">
        <section class="terms-card">

            <p class="terms-label">SKOLAR PLATFORM</p>
            <h1>Terms and Conditions for Students & Guardians</h1>
            <p class="updated-text">Effective Date: June 2026 | Version 1.1</p>

            <div class="terms-content">
                <p>
                    Welcome to Skolar. By registering an account as a user or a supervising
                    parent/guardian, you accept and agree to comply with these Terms and Conditions.
                    These policies guarantee a fair, reliable, and mutually respectful atmosphere
                    for both students and educators.
                </p>

                <h2>1. Eligibility and Guardian Responsibility</h2>
                <p>
                    Safety is Skolar's highest operational priority. All platform participants must
                    verify their identity.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Mandatory Verification:</strong> Students are required to provide a valid,
                        unexpired government-issued photo identity document upon registration.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Minor Policy (Under 18):</strong> If the student is a minor, a parent or
                        legal guardian must create and manage the account. The guardian must upload their
                        own valid government photo ID and is legally responsible for monitoring all platform
                        activities, communications, and scheduling.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Data Security:</strong> All identification documentation is fully encrypted,
                        securely stored, and reviewed strictly by Skolar Administration. It will never be
                        exposed to tutors or other third parties.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>2. Session Structure Requirements</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Minimum Session Duration:</strong> To maximize learning efficacy and respect
                        educators' schedules, all bookings require a minimum length of one (1) hour per
                        session. Shorter time frames or partial checkouts are not supported by the platform.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Student Cancellation and Refund Tiers</h2>
                <p>
                    Tutors dedicate specific slots in their professional schedules to accommodate your
                    sessions. Late student cancellations directly impact their livelihood. Refund structures
                    are governed by the notice provided below:
                </p>

                <div class="terms-table-wrap">
                    <table class="terms-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Cancellation Timeline</th>
                                <th>Refund Entitlement</th>
                                <th>Account Consequences / Penalties</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>

                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>3+ Days Before Session</strong><br>
                                    <span>72+ hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td><strong>100% Refund</strong></td>
                                <td>
                                    1 official advanced cancellation warning issued to monitor scheduling stability.
                                </td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>2 Days Before Session</strong><br>
                                    <span>48 to 72 hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td><strong>70% Refund</strong></td>
                                <td>
                                    No warning issued. 30% is retained to partially compensate the tutor for holding the slot.
                                </td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>1 Day Before Session</strong><br>
                                    <span>24 to 48 hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td><strong>50% Refund</strong></td>
                                <td>
                                    No warning issued. 50% is retained as tutor compensation for the reserved schedule.
                                </td>
                            </tr>

                            <tr>
                                <td>
                                    <strong>Same-Day Cancellation</strong><br>
                                    <span>Less than 24 hours notice</span>
                                </td>
                                <td><strong>50% Refund</strong></td>
                                <td>
                                    No warning issued. 50% is retained to compensate the tutor for a completely lost slot.
                                </td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>

                <h3>3.1 Advanced Cancellation Warning System</h3>
                <p>
                    While providing more than 3 days' notice grants a full financial refund, excessive
                    cancellations disrupt tutor schedules and platform resource allocation.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Each 3+ day cancellation registers an official system warning.</li>
                    <li>
                        Every third (3rd) warning an account accumulates will automatically reduce the
                        student's next 3+ day cancellation refund from 100% down to 50% only. Subsequent
                        warnings reset the tracking block.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="info-box">
                    <h3>💡 Tutor Cancellation Protections for Students</h3>
                    <p>
                        If a tutor cancels less than 24 hours before the session, you are fully protected.
                        You receive a 100% refund request plus a 20% discount voucher for your next
                        qualifying 2-hour session booking. The refund is completed after provider confirmation.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="warning-box">
                    <h3>⚠ Anti-Circumvention Rule</h3>
                    <p>
                        To protect your financial security and privacy, all scheduling, communications,
                        and financial exchange must take place strictly inside Skolar. Engaging in
                        off-platform cash or app payments, or exchanging direct contact details to bypass
                        platform protections, constitutes a major violation and results in the immediate
                        and irreversible closure of your account.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2>4. Payment and Refund Processing</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar is designed to process payments through an authorized third-party payment provider.
                    Payment credentials such as card numbers, e-wallet PINs, and banking passwords must be handled
                    by the payment provider and must not be stored by Skolar.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Session charge:</strong> tutor hourly rate × session duration.</li>
                    <li><strong>Date-range total:</strong> session charge × number of selected sessions.</li>
                    <li><strong>Refund amount:</strong> affected session amount × applicable refund percentage.</li>
                    <li>Refunds for date-range bookings are calculated separately for each cancelled session.</li>
                    <li>A refund is complete only after the connected payment provider confirms it.</li>
                </ul>

                <p>
                    Payment and refund statuses may include Pending, Paid, Processing, Partially Refunded,
                    Refunded, Failed, and Requires Review once the payment API is connected.
                </p>

                <h2>5. Exclusive Administrative Review</h2>
                <p>
                    Any and all complaints, disputes, tutor misconduct reports, or fee discrepancies must
                    be submitted exclusively to the Skolar Administration.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Students and guardians agree that administrative intervention is the designated path
                        for dispute resolution.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        All decisions rendered by Skolar Administration regarding cancellations, partial
                        refunds, warning distribution, or user suspensions are final, absolute, and binding.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>6. Academic Integrity Code</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar is an educational growth tool designed to foster self-sufficiency. Students are
                    expected to uphold the rules of their primary academic institutions.
                </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Students may not demand, request, or coerce tutors into completing graded homework,
                        writing papers, or taking tests on their behalf.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Using Skolar services to commit academic fraud or cheating will cause immediate
                        administrative review and potential account suspension.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>7. Liability Disclaimer</h2>
                <p>
                    Skolar serves as an intermediary platform connecting users. We ensure identity validation
                    and secure environments but are not liable for specific test scores, classroom grades,
                    or individual tutor methods. Users must treat all educators with respect during live
                    video interfaces.
                </p>
            </div>

            <a href="@Url.Action("Signup", "Home")?role=learner" class="agree-btn">Back to Learner Sign Up</a>
        </section>
    </main>

</body>
</html>
